The core changes are:
1. Added `_has_protected_files()` - checks if a task's files include any protected implementation files (evolve.sh, format_issues.py, build_site.py, self-assess SKILL.md, evolve SKILL.md)
2. Added `_ANALYSIS_ONLY_METRICS` constant and `_has_analysis_only_pressure()` - detects when the assessment shows "analysis-only" pressure (tasks where the agent only analyzed but didn't edit)
3. In `choose_task()`, added two gates:
   - Skip tasks that touch protected files (so they never get seeded)
   - When analysis-only pressure exists, suppress the lifecycle task (because analysis-only pressure takes priority)

The issue this fixes: When the preseed task planner detects analysis-only task pressure (where the agent is spending sessions analyzing but not editing code), it should prioritize that pressure — it shouldn't get drowned out by the lifecycle cleanup task. Also, the planner should never propose tasks that touch protected implementation files.

